column5: Anybody catching yet? By Picton or main bay already?  Thanks!!!
There's always walleye in Quinte, and it's always worth going.

Just go man...  I'm going tomorrow... And not knowing is part of the fun...  Ill have a hard time sleeping because I'm still trying to figure out where to start my day... 2 rods each or 1.... Deep or shallow.... Fast or slow.... What cranks.... Regular or decaf...lol  And it can change day to day...

I believe that there is a walleye tournament there this weekend.To answer your questions Mike...... 2 rods, go deep, real slow, reef runners, manns stretch 20s and X large with 2 milk 1 sugar. Hope that helps you sleep better
